    <name>
      <text>Representing data using a grouped frequency distribution table</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>The following data represents the exam scores of <strong>{@total_students@}</strong> students in a mathematics class:</p>

<p style="background-color: #f9f9f9; padding: 15px; border: 1px solid #ddd; font-family: monospace; font-size: 1.1em; line-height: 1.6;">
    {@data_str@}
</p>

<p>Construct a <strong>grouped frequency distribution table</strong> for this data using the class intervals provided below.</p>

<table class="table table-bordered table-striped" style="width: 60%; margin-top: 20px;">
    <thead style="background-color: #e0e0e0;">
        <tr>
            <th style="text-align: center;">Score Interval</th>
            <th style="text-align: center;">Frequency</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td style="text-align: center;">{@c1_min@} – {@c1_max@}</td>
            <td style="text-align: center;">[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="text-align: center;">{@c2_min@} – {@c2_max@}</td>
            <td style="text-align: center;">[[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="text-align: center;">{@c3_min@} – {@c3_max@}</td>
            <td style="text-align: center;">[[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]]</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="text-align: center;">{@c4_min@} – {@c4_max@}</td>
            <td style="text-align: center;">[[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]]</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="text-align: center;">{@c5_min@} – {@c5_max@}</td>
            <td style="text-align: center;">[[input:ans5]] [[validation:ans5]]</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="font-weight: bold; background-color: #f2f2f2;">
            <td style="text-align: right; padding-right: 20px;">Total</td>
            <td style="text-align: center;">[[input:ans_total]] [[validation:ans_total]]</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
[[feedback:prt1]]]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>
<p>To create the grouped frequency table, you tally the scores that fall into each range:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>{@c1_min@} – {@c1_max@}:</strong> Counting scores in the 40s gives <strong>{@f1@}</strong>.</li>
    <li><strong>{@c2_min@} – {@c2_max@}:</strong> Counting scores in the 50s gives <strong>{@f2@}</strong>.</li>
    <li><strong>{@c3_min@} – {@c3_max@}:</strong> Counting scores in the 60s gives <strong>{@f3@}</strong>.</li>
    <li><strong>{@c4_min@} – {@c4_max@}:</strong> Counting scores in the 70s gives <strong>{@f4@}</strong>.</li>
    <li><strong>{@c5_min@} – {@c5_max@}:</strong> Counting scores in the 80s gives <strong>{@f5@}</strong>.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Total Check:</strong> {@f1@} + {@f2@} + {@f3@} + {@f4@} + {@f5@} = <strong>{@total_students@}</strong>.</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
